data.description: Enjoy all that The Waters has to offer in this 3 bed, 3 1/2 bath cottage with owner's suites on the 1st and 2nd floors. Sit on your front porch and look at 200 acre Lake Cameron or just chat with your neighbors. The convenient side yard is fenced with both a flagstone patio and large deck for grilling and private entertainment. Graced with wood floors and tile, the great room, dining room and kitchen are open to one another yet separated with just enough of a cased opening to suggest separate spaces. Tall windows flood the space with natural light making the 1st floor airy and bright. The great room features a fireplace with gas logs, The kitchen features a 36" gas range and large work island with a separate sink. Your study/office provides access to the deck and side yard and separates the 1st floor owner's suite from the rest of the house. This space also contains a second laundry area providing convenient laundry access. Your owner's suite includes a large walk-in closet and bath with double vanity, jetted soaking tub and separate shower. Upstairs there is a second laundry closet, a second owner's suite with a shower only and a third suite with a tub/shower. The owner has recently replaced all HVAC systems with high efficiency units. Downstairs is served by a tankless gas water heater and the upstairs by a separate electric tank unit. All bedrooms are spacious with large closets. This property offers an ASSUMABLE low-interest mortgage to a qualified buyer. Vacation at home - World class fishing, lake boating, 2 swimming pools, 5 tennis courts, 2 pickle ball courts, lakeside beach, dog park, town square, fire pit, soccer field, playborhood hill, bocce ball, pavilions, sport court, gaga pit, kayaking, canoeing, playgrounds, parks, 2.5 miles off I-85, Exit 16 & less than 15 min. to The Shops at Pike Road & Chantilly Pkwy. Zoned for Pike Road Schools, K4-12th grade. Seller has right to approve buyer’s mortgage lender.
